title: Prosise leads Notre Dame over Navy
text:
Prosise leads Notre Dame over Navy 
By WISE Web Sports University of Notre Dame Fighting Irish October 10, 2015 Updated Oct 10, 2015 at 10:46 PM EDT 
(South Bend, Indiana) -- Notre Dame running back C.J. Prosise made Navy pay for its turnovers. Prosise scored one play after linebacker Jaylon Smith recovered a fumble by Chris Swain on the Navy seven yard line and two plays after Devin Butler recovered a fumble by Dishan Romine at the 26 - yard line on the opening kickoff of the second half. He finished with three rushing touchdowns as the 15th - ranked Fighting Irish beat the Midshipmen 41 - 24 on Saturday. Prosise finished with 129 yards rushing to help the Fighting Irish improve to 5 - 1 for the season.   To submit a comment on this article, your email address is required.
